title: Introduction to rbin
text: Binning process transforming numerical continuous data categorical data. common data pre-processing step model building process. rbin following features: manual binning using shiny app equal length binning method winsorized binning method quantile binning method combine levels categorical data create dummy variables based binning method calculates weight evidence (WOE), entropy information value (IV) provides summary information binning pre-processing

title: Introduction to rbin
text: manual binning, need specify cut points bins. rbin follows left closed right open interval ([0,1) = {x | 0 ≤ x < 1}) creating bins. number cut points specify one less number bins want create .e. want create 10 bins, need specify 9 cut points shown example. accompanying RStudio addin, rbinAddin() can used iteratively bin data enforce monotonic increasing/decreasing trend. finalizing bins, can use rbin_create() create dummy variables.
